This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a novel multi-task learning system that combines appearance and motion cues for semantic reasoning of the environment. The paper also focuses on vehicle detection and motion segmentation, which are common tasks in autonomous driving (cs.RO). The use of a shared encoder for both tasks suggests that the paper may also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper utilizes a dataset and benchmarks for evaluation, indicating that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with video sequences and segmentation, which are common topics in multimedia (cs.MM).
